.TH "iio_buffer_poll" 9 "iio_buffer_poll" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
iio_buffer_poll \- poll the buffer to find out if it has data
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "__poll_t" iio_buffer_poll
.BI "(struct file *filp "  ","
.BI "struct poll_table_struct *wait "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "filp" 12
File structure pointer for device access
.IP "wait" 12
Poll table structure pointer for which the driver adds
a wait queue
.SH "RETURN"
(EPOLLIN | EPOLLRDNORM) if data is available for reading
or 0 for other cases
